{{Refimprove|date=March 2014}} {{Infobox park | name = Sitakunda Botanical Garden and Eco Park | alt_name = Sitakunda Eco Park | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Entrance of Botanical Garden and Eco Park (1).JPG | image_size = 220px | image_caption = Entrance | map = Bangladesh | map_width = 200px | map_caption = Location in Bangladesh | relief = | label = | label_position = | mark = | mark_width = | type = [[Urban park]] | motto = | location = [[Muradpur Upazilla|Muradpur]], [[Sitakunda]], [[Chittagong]], Bangladesh | nearest_city = | nearest_town = | grid_ref_UK = | grid_ref_Ireland = | coordinates = {{Coord|22.6016315|91.6715161|region:BD_type:forest|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{Convert|996|acre}} | elevation = | authorized = | created = | established = 2001 | designated = | opened = | opening = | closed = | founder = | designer = | etymology = | owner = | administrator = | manager = | operator = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | open = 10:00-20:00 | status = open all year | awards = | camp_sites = | hiking_trails = | paths = | terrain = | habitat = | water = | plants = | vegetation = | species = | collections = | designation = | disturbance = | budget = | parking = | publictransit = | transport = Muradpur Bus Stop | free_label = | free_data = | other_info = There is charge for 20 taka except children. | facilities = | website = | embedded = | child = }}
'''Sitakunda Botanical Garden and Eco Park''' is a park located in [[Sitakunda Upazila]] of [[Chittagong District]] in south-eastern [[Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Islam |first=Md Mojaharul |year=2012 |chapter=Ecopark |chapter-url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Ecopark |editor1-last=Islam |editor1-first=Sirajul |editor1-link=Sirajul Islam |editor2-last=Jamal |editor2-first=Ahmed A. |title=Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |edition=Second |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]]}}</ref>
== History == This is the first eco-park in Bangladesh. It was established in 2001 on 808 hectares. The main purposes of creating such eco parks are storing biodiversity, conservation. <ref>{{cite web|title= Establishment of Sitakund Eco Park|url=http://truelybangladesh.blogspot.com/2013/03/sitakunda-eco-park.html?m=1}}</ref>
==Area and location== The Sitakunda Botanical Garden and Eco Park is located along the [[Dhaka–Chittagong Highway]] in [[Sitakunda Upazila]], [[Sitakunda]], Chittagong. The area of Eco Park is about {{Convert|996|acre}} which is established at forest side of [[Chandranath Hills]] of Sitakunda.<ref name="parjatanbd1">{{cite web|url=http://www.parjatanbd.com/print_details.php?id=20 |title=Sitakunda Eco Park |publisher=Parjatanbd.com |date= |accessdate=2014-03-03}}</ref>
== Key attractions ==
{| class="wikitable" |- !Thematic areas !Details |- | Lake Front || Spine of the Eco Park, pine-tree lined pathway designed for the visitors to enjoy the beauty of the water bodies such as the [[pond]] that defines the park. |- | Tropical Tree Garden|| As the name suggests, this zone caters specifically to tropical trees. |- | Wild|| There are deer, bears, monkeys and birds such as [[doyel]], parrots, swallows, herons and sparrows. Monkeys move always among the bamboo and some large trees.<ref name="parjatanbd1"/> |- | Wild Flower Meadow and Formal Garden || A flower lover’s zone, these two areas will have varieties of both garden and wild flowers to enjoy. |- | Fruits Garden|| A thematic zone dedicated to the Bengal delicacy of fruits, to showcase the bountiful nature of this part of earth and to encourage nature learning through identification of fruit bearing trees. |- | Food Court|| There are about twenty food courts for refreshment in front of the park entrance. |}
==Facilities== Presently there are parking lots for Eco Park. Toilet facilities are available for free in three locations. There is a plant nursery selling Bangladeshi and foreign plants.
