'''Jan Esper''' (born 1968) <ref>{{cite web|title=Homepage of Jan Esper |url=http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/ |accessdate=2007-02-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070528034744/http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/ |archivedate=2007-05-28 |df= }}</ref> is the head of the dendro sciences division at the WSL (Wald Snee und Landschafft - en:Forest, Snow and Landscape) division of the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology ([[ETH]]). His research interests are [[Global Climate Change]], [[Palaeoclimatology]] and Vegetation Dynamics.
His research has been part of the [[Hockey stick controversy]] with his temperature reconstructions, that have been cited as being evidence for both sides of the controversy.
== Academic career == * 1995 Diplom in Geography at [[University of Bonn]] * 1999 Ph.D. in Geography at the [[University of Bonn]] * 2000 Postdoc at [[Columbia University]] * 2001 Research scientist at [[ETH]], [[Birmensdorf]] * 2005 [[Habilitation]] at the [[University of Bern]] * 2006 Head Dendro Sciences Division, WSL (Wald Schnee und Landschaft)
== Selected publications == * {{Cite journal |first1=M.N. |last=Juckes |first2=M.R. |last2=Allen |first3=Keith R. |last3=Briffa |first4=Jan |last4=Esper |first5=G.C. |last5=Hegerl |first6=Anders |last6=Moberg |first7=Timothy J. |last7=Osborn |first8=S.L. |last8=Weber |first9=Eduardo |last9=Zorita |authorlink4=Jan Esper |title=Millennial temperature reconstruction intercomparison and evaluation |journal=Climate of the Past Discussions |volume=2 |issue=5 |pages=1001–1049 |url=http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/publications/Juckes_2007_CP.pdf |format=pdf |doi=10.5194/cpd-2-1001-2006 |year=2006 |postscript= }}{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} * {{Cite journal |first1=Jan |last1=Esper |first2=Robert J.S. |last2=Wilson |first3=David C. |last3=Frank |first4=Anders |last4=Moberg |first5=Heinz |last5=Wanner |first6=Jürg |last6=Luterbacher |author1-link=Jan Esper |title=Climate: past ranges and future changes |journal=Quaternary Science Reviews |year=2005 |volume=24 |issue=20–21 |pages=2164–2166 |url=http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/publications/QSR_Esper_2005.pdf |doi=10.1016/j.quascirev.2005.07.001 |postscript= |bibcode=2005QSRv...24.2164E |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061230223535/http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/publications/QSR_Esper_2005.pdf |archivedate=2006-12-30 |df= }} * {{Cite journal |first1=Jan |last1=Esper |first2=Edward R. |last2=Cook |first3=Fritz H. |last3=Schweingruber |author1-link=Jan Esper |title=Low-frequency signals in long tree-ring chronologies and the reconstruction of past temperature variability |journal=[[Science (journal)|Science]] |year=2002 |volume=295 |issue=5563 |pages=2250–2253 |url=http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/publications/Science_2002.pdf |doi=10.1126/science.1066208 |pmid=11910106 |postscript= |bibcode=2002Sci...295.2250E |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070221081646/http://www.wsl.ch/staff/jan.esper/publications/Science_2002.pdf |archivedate=2007