{{Expand section|date=September 2015}}

The '''Semantic Geospatial Web''' or '''Geospatial Semantic Web''' is a vision to include geospatial information at the core of the [[Semantic Web]] to facilitate [[information retrieval]] and [[information integration]].<ref>{{Cite journal|title = Toward the Semantic Geospatial Web|url = http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/585147.585148|publisher = ACM|journal = Proceedings of the 10th ACM International Symposium on Advances in Geographic Information Systems|date = 2002-01-01|location = New York, NY, USA|isbn = 1-58113-591-2|pages = 1–4|series = GIS '02|doi = 10.1145/585147.585148|first = Max J.|last = Egenhofer}}</ref> This vision requires the definition of geospatial [[Ontology (information science)|ontologies]], semantic [[gazetteer]]s, and shared technical vocabularies to describe [[Geographic data|geographic phenomena]].<ref>{{Cite book|title = A Geo-semantics Flyby|url = https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-39784-4_6|publisher = Springer Berlin Heidelberg|date = 2013-01-01|isbn = 978-3-642-39783-7|pages = 230–250|series = Lecture Notes in Computer Science|doi = 10.1007/978-3-642-39784-4_6#page-1|first = Krzysztof|last = Janowicz|first2 = Simon|last2 = Scheider|first3 = Benjamin|last3 = Adams|editor-first = Sebastian|editor-last = Rudolph|editor-first2 = Georg|editor-last2 = Gottlob|editor-first3 = Ian|editor-last3 = Horrocks|editor-first4 = Frank van|display-editors = 3 |editor-last4 = Harmelen}}</ref> The Semantic Geospatial Web is part of [[geographic information science]].

